"title": "1670: symbols",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1670",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Objects, actions or creatures that have a deeper significance and are so understood by those who see them or use them.</p>\n<h2>Symbolic objects</h2>\n<h3>The rainbow: a symbol of God's covenant</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:13\">GEN 9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:3\">REV 4:3</a></p>\n<h3>A stairway: a symbol of the way to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:11-Gen28:13\">GEN 28:11–28:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:51\">JHN 1:51</a></p>\n<h3>Thunder, lightning, cloud and smoke: symbols of God's majesty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:18\">EXO 19:16–19:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:17\">EXO 24:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:2\">PSA 97:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:4\">PSA 97:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">REV 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:5\">REV 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:19\">REV 11:19</a></p>\n<h3>Thunder: a symbol of God's voice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:3\">PSA 29:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:33\">PSA 68:33</a></p>\n<h3>Trumpets: a symbol of God speaking</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:19\">EXO 19:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:6\">REV 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>The pillar of cloud and fire: a symbol of guidance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:21\">EXO 13:21</a></p>\n<h3>A throne:  a symbol of God's glory</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:26\">EZK 1:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:2\">REV 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3\">REV 22:3</a></p>\n<h3>Dry bones: a symbol of spiritual death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:1-Ezek37:2\">EZK 37:1–37:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:11\">EZK 37:11</a></p>\n<h3>White hair: a symbol of wisdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:14\">REV 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>The wind: a symbol of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:8\">JHN 3:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:2\">ACT 2:2</a></p>\n<h3>Fire: a symbol of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:3\">ACT 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Stars and lampstands: symbols of God's ministers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:20\">REV 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>A signet ring: a symbol of authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:10\">EST 8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:23\">HAG 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Arrows: symbols of God's judgments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:2\">PSA 38:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps120:4\">PSA 120:4</a></p>\n<h3>A sceptre: a symbol of God's rule</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:9\">PSA 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:27\">REV 2:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:15\">REV 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>The capstone: a symbol of pre-eminence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:42\">MAT 21:42</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:10-Mark12:11\">MRK 12:10–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:17\">LUK 20:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:22\">PSA 118:22</a></p>\n<h3>A rock: a symbol of stability</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:2\">PSA 40:2</a></p>\n<h3>The human body: a symbol of interdependence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a></p>\n<h3>Grass: a symbol of human frailty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:5-Ps90:6\">PSA 90:5–90:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:24\">1PE 1:24</a></p>\n<h2>Symbolic creatures</h2>\n<h3>The serpent: a symbol of Satan's subtlety</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1\">GEN 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">REV 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1-Rev20:3\">REV 20:1–20:3</a></p>\n<h3>Locusts: a symbol of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:12\">EXO 10:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:4\">JOL 1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:3\">REV 9:3</a></p>\n<h3>Beasts: symbols of earthly kingdoms</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2-Dan7:7\">DAN 7:2–7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:17\">DAN 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:20-Dan8:22\">DAN 8:20–8:22</a></p>\n<h3>A dove: a symbol of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16\">MAT 3:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10\">MRK 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>A lamb: a symbol of Jesus Christ's sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a></p>\n<h2>Symbolic actions</h2>\n<h3>Breaking a jar: a symbol of the destruction of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:10-Jer19:11\">JER 19:10–19:11</a></p>\n<h3>The cursing of a fig-tree: a symbol of judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18-Matt21:19\">MAT 21:18–21:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12-Mark11:14\">MRK 11:12–11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Washing hands: a symbol of innocence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a></p>\n<h3>Being thirsty: a symbol of spiritual need</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:1\">PSA 63:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37\">JHN 7:37</a></p>\n<h3>Baptism: a symbol of salvation in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:3-Rom6:4\">ROM 6:3–6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>The Lord's Supper: a symbol of union with Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:29\">MAT 26:26–26:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:22–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:19–22:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:23–11:26</a></p>\n<h3>Anointing: a symbol of empowering by God's Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a></p>\n<h3>Harvesting: a symbol of judgment day</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:12-Joel3:13\">JOL 3:12–3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:29-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:29–13:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:15\">REV 14:15</a></p>\n<h3>Tearing garments: a symbol of anger and sorrow</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:29\">GEN 37:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:34\">GEN 37:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">JOS 7:6</a></p>\n<h3>Spitting: a symbol of contempt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:6\">ISA 50:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67\">MAT 26:67</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:65\">MRK 14:65</a></p>\n<h3>Shaking off dust: a symbol of rejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:14\">MAT 10:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:5\">LUK 9:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:51\">ACT 13:51</a></p>\n<h3>Sitting in sackcloth and ashes: a symbol of repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:11\">PSA 69:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:12\">ISA 22:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:5-Jonah3:6\">JON 3:5–3:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:21\">MAT 11:21</a></p>\n<h3>Lifting of hands: a symbol of prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:4\">PSA 63:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:8\">1TI 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Covering the head: a symbol of submission</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3-1Cor11:10\">1CO 11:3–11:10</a></p>\n<h2>Symbols expressing God's nature and character</h2>\n<h3>God's face: a symbol of his presence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:25-Num6:26\">NUM 6:25–6:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:16\">PSA 34:16</a></p>\n<h3>God's arm or hand: a symbol of his power</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:8\">PSA 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:13\">PSA 89:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's eyes: a symbol of his awareness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:3\">PRO 15:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>God's ear: a symbol of God listening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:2\">PSA 31:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1\">ISA 59:1</a></p>",
